org.openbel.framework.core.df
Class AbstractJdbcDAO

java.lang.Object
  org.openbel.framework.core.df.AbstractJdbcDAO
Direct Known Subclasses:
JdbcKAMLoaderImpl, KAMCatalogDao, KAMStoreDaoImpl, KAMStoreStatisticsDaoImpl
public abstract class AbstractJdbcDAO
extends Object

AbstractJdbcDataAccessor provides low-level JDBC operations for working with a database.

The PreparedStatement objects used are cached to avoid repeated statement compilation and increase application performance.

Author:
Anthony Bargnesi <abargnesi@selventa.com>

getPreparedStatement

protected PreparedStatement getPreparedStatement(String sql,
                                                 int autoGeneratedKeys)
                                          throws SQLException
Returns the PreparedStatement wrapping a sql statement in sql.

The prepared statement's autoGeneratedKeys feature is set via the additional parameter.

Parameters:
sql - String the sql statement to use in the PreparedStatement, which can take parameter substitutions - '?'.
autoGeneratedKeys - int the auto generated keys feature in the PreparedStatement
Returns:
PreparedStatement the prepared statement, which could be either new or cached
Throws:
SQLException - Thrown if a database exception occurred or if the dbConnection is no longer valid and cannot be re-established
